    Admin/ContentController

    posts

    List all posts

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://localhost/admin/content/posts" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/content/posts",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    postsOfCategory

    List all posts of a category

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://localhost/admin/content/posts-of-category/{id}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/content/posts-of-category/{id}",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    GET admin/content/{content}

    HEAD admin/content/{content}

    update

    Update the specified content

    Example request:

    curl -X PUT "http://localhost/admin/content/{content}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/content/{content}",
    "method": "PUT",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    GET admin/price-element/{price_element}

    HEAD admin/price-element/{price_element}

    update

    Update the specified PriceElement

    Example request:

    curl -X PUT "http://localhost/admin/price-element/{price_element}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/price-element/{price_element}",
    "method": "PUT",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HEAD admin/user

    store

    Store a newly created User

    Example request:

    curl -X POST "http://localhost/admin/user" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/user",
    "method": "POST",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    POST admin/user

    show

    Display the specified User

    Example request:

-H "Accept: application/json"

    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/user/{user}",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    GET admin/user/{user}

    HEAD admin/user/{user}

    update

    Update the specified User

    Example request:

    curl -X PUT "http://localhost/admin/user/{user}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/user/{user}",
    "method": "PUT",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    PUT admin/user/{user}

    HTTP Request

    GET admin/device/{device}

    HEAD admin/device/{device}

    update

    Update the specified Device

    Example request:

    curl -X PUT "http://localhost/admin/device/{device}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"

    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/device/{device}",

        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

    console.log(response);

    HTTP Request

    GET admin/organization/{organization}

    HEAD admin/organization/{organization}

    destroy

    Remove the specified Organization

    Example request:

    curl -X DELETE "http://localhost/admin/organization/{organization}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/admin/organization/{organization}",
    "method": "DELETE",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    DELETE admin/organization/{organization}

    HotelSearchController

    index

    curl -X POST "http://localhost/hotel-search" \
-H "Accept: application/json"

    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/hotel-search",
    "method": "POST",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    GET stylersmedia/gallery-item/{gallery_item}

    HEAD stylersmedia/gallery-item/{gallery_item}

    update

    Update the specified GalleryItem by File ID

    Example request:

    curl -X PUT "http://localhost/stylersmedia/gallery-item/{gallery_item}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/stylersmedia/gallery-item/{gallery_item}",
    "method": "PUT",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    GET stylerstaxonomy/description

    HEAD stylerstaxonomy/description

    show

    Display a specified Description

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/description/{description}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/description/{description}",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    Example response:

    {
    "success": true,
    "data": {
        "id": 1,
        "description": "Hotel A",
        "created_at": "2017-05-12 08:39:02",
        "updated_at": "2017-05-12 08:39:02",
        "deleted_at": null
    }
}

    HTTP Request

    GET stylerstaxonomy/description/{description}

    HEAD stylerstaxonomy/description/{description}

    Stylerstaxonomy/TaxonomyController

    setPriorities

    Sets priority of all specified Taxonomies by their order in request

    Example request:

    curl -X PUT "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/priorities" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/priorities",
    "method": "PUT",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    PUT stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/priorities

    store

    Store a new Taxonomy

    Example request:

    curl -X POST "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy",
    "method": "POST",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    POST stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy

    update

    Update a specified Taxonomy

    Example request:

    curl -X PUT "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/{taxonomy}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/{taxonomy}",
    "method": "PUT",

    HTTP Request

    GET stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/siblings/{id}

    HEAD stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/siblings/{id}

    index

    List all Taxonomies

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});

    HTTP Request

    GET stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy

    HEAD stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy

    show

    Display a specified Taxonomy

    Example request:

    curl -X GET "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/{taxonomy}" \
-H "Accept: application/json"
    var settings = {
    "async": true,
    "crossDomain": true,
    "url": "http://localhost/stylerstaxonomy/taxonomy/{taxonomy}",
    "method": "GET",
    "headers": {
        "accept": "application/json"
    }
}

$.ajax(settings).done(function (response) {
    console.log(response);
});
